attributes.gcd: Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.
Flag identifies the latest records for a particular combination of primary keys. List of values are Y and N.

Refers to the load run identifier. Load run identifier enables user to load multiple versions intraday or post back dated adjustment entries to the table. Refers to the Load run identifier of the equivalent record in product processor that needs to be adjusted. Default value of  1 indicates that the latest load run is being adjusted.

This is the unique identifier of the policy held by the customer. An insurance policy identifier or number is a unique identifier provided by insurance company which is used to identify particular contract between insurance company and policyholder wherein insurance company accepts to cover specific risks in return of premium payments by policyholder as per terms and agreements. The policy number can be referenced from policy document and needs to be quoted with all communication with insurance company.
Refers to the code applicable to the Rating Source along with Horizon separated by a space. E.g. FIT L, FIT S.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.
This is the unique identifier of the vehicle associated with the auto insurance policy or claim process.
Refers to the vehicle rating code. Vehicle ratings are used to estimate vehicle insurance amount, damage rating leading to premium amount based on vehicle condition.
This column stores any applicable sub class codes as outlined in the Company rating manuals.
